attributes.comment:
One time I as a patient seeking a new gynecologist, requested a “female doctor” and it was only after my appointment was done, I realized the doctor was a MTF or trans male to female. In other words, a male.

I felt hurt, betrayed and scared by the fact that my healthcare provider assigned me a male doctor when I asked for a woman. Never have I forgotten the shock I felt, and I never returned to that practitioner.

It matters to me whether I see a male or female gynecologist, as some contexts like that, really do demand transparency in disclosing biological sex.
